init_text:
Are We Being Bad Citizens If We Don't Keep Up With the News?

In your opinion, are we being bad citizens if we don't keep up with the news? Do you think all people have some responsibility to know what is going on in the world? Does engaging with current events actually do anything at all? Why do you think the way you do?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I think that it is important to know what is going on in the world, and to be aware of the issues that are affecting people around you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If you are going to be talking about the news, you need to know what you are talking about.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If everyone were to be more informed, and more aware of the world around them, I think that we could make a huge difference.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I think that we are all responsible for keeping up with current events, to some degree.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But they don't do anything about it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: is the responsible thing to do.
